      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "I think that `addr_man` is not in a usable state if an exception is thrown (i.e. it is in an undefined state). Below we call its methods and expect they would work. Maybe:\r\n```suggestion\r\n        try {\r\n            ds >> addr_man;\r\n        } catch (const std::ios_base::failure&) {\r\n            addr_man.Clear();\r\n        }\r\n```",
